         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2999_1.jpg"/>

            <note rend="pencil" hand="other">
               <p>[17 July 1923]</p>
            </note>



            <opener>





               <salute>My dear Tom,</salute>

            </opener>


            <p>Will you be kind enough to tell me if the <persName ref="#ps:EdwardWindsor">Prince of
                  Wales</persName> will enter <placeName ref="#pl:Dorchester">Dorchester</placeName>
               by way of <placeName ref="#pl:StinsfordHill">Stinsford Hill</placeName> &amp; if so
               at <hi rend="underline">about</hi> what time he will be passing thereon. We hear so
               many different reports, and of course the <orgName ref="#ps:TheTimes" rend="italics"
                  >Times</orgName> for today has got lost somewhere in the post â€“ the report is that
                  <persName ref="#ps:EdwardWindsor"><choice>
                     <abbr>H. R. H.</abbr>
                     <expan>His Royal Highness</expan></choice></persName> is not coming at all on
               account of the small pox creeping around!!!!</p>

            <p>All workfolk about here are given three hours to go to <placeName
                  ref="#pl:Dorchester"><choice><abbr>D.</abbr>
                     <expan>Dorchester</expan></choice></placeName>, so <persName ref="#ps:Chutter"
                  >Chutter</persName> will go, &amp; his daughter who is at service at <persName
                  ref="#ps:HarryChristopher">Harry Christopher</persName>'s has a ticket for the
               Drill Hall (<persName ref="#ps:HarryChristopher"><choice><abbr>H.C.</abbr>
                     <expan>Harry Christopher</expan></choice></persName> has something to do with
               the police force.) Lots of people are going "to have a good look at en' when he gets
               to <placeName ref="#pl:MaxGate">Max Gate</placeName> so you had better be well
               guarded.</p>

            <p><persName ref="#ps:HenryHardy">Henry</persName> wishes me to <pb n="2"
                  facs="uoedh_hl_h.2999_2.jpg"/> ask you if it will be right for us to put up the
               Union Jack. We hope you are both feeling "all for it" and are quite well. </p>



            <closer>

               <salute>Best love to both</salute>
               <salute>Yours affectionately</salute>
               <signed>Katharine.</signed>
               <note rend="pencil" hand="other">(sister)</note>
            </closer>






         </div>
